## What IS allowed (Non-Commercial Use):

✅ **Personal use** — Use at home for yourself
✅ **Educational use** — Use in schools, universities (non-profit)
✅ **Research** — Academic and scientific research
✅ **Hobby projects** — Personal learning and experimentation
✅ **Open source contributions** — Contributing back to this project
✅ **Non-profit organizations** — Use by registered non-profits
✅ **Sharing** — Sharing with friends, family, community
✅ **Teaching** — Using in free courses or workshops

### Examples of Non-Commercial Use (Allowed):

- Using AntiStutter at home for personal stuttering reduction
- Using in university research projects
- Adapting for a school science project
- Contributing improvements back to this repository
- Using in a free, non-profit stuttering support group
- Teaching others how to use it in free workshops

